<h3>Bibliography</h3>

<p class="bibl">Bennett, Shelley M. <span class="book"> Thomas Stothard: the Mechanisms 
of Art Patronage in England circa 1800</span>. Columbia: University of Missouri Press, 
1988.</p>

<p class="bibl">Bray, Mrs. <span class="book">Life of Thomas Stothard, R. A., with 
Personal Reminiscences</span>. London: John Murray, 1851.</p>

<p class="bibl">Coxhead, Albert Crease. <span class="book"> Thomas Stothard, R.A., an
Illustrated Monograph</span>. London: A. H. Bullen, 1906.</p>

<p class="bibl">Defoe, Daniel. <span class="book">The Life and Adventures of Robinson 
Crusoe, Written by Himself</span>. Illustrated by Thomas Stothard; engraving by C. Heath. 
London: Bliss, Sands, and Foster, 1820.</p>

<p class="bibl">Goldsmith, Dr. [Oliver]. <span class="book">The Vicar of Wakefield. A 
Tale</span>. Illustrated by Thomas Stothard. London: Sammells and Ritchie for E. Harding, 
Fleet-Street;  and J. Good, New Bond-Street, 1792.</p>

<p class="bibl">Ray, Gordon N. <span class="book">The Illustrator and the Book in 
England from 1790 to 1914</span>. New York: Pierpont Morgan Library and Oxford University 
Press, n. d.</p>

<p class="bibl">Sterne, Laurence. <span class="book">A Sentimental Journey through France
and Italy by Mr. Yorick</span>. Illustrated by Thomas Stothard. London: J. Good, No. 159,
New Bond Street; and E. and S. Harding, No. 102, Pall Mall, 1792; rpt., 1801].</p>

